<file path="prompt.md">
Implement the private `apply_event/2` function. It is the "left fold" reducer of the
event-sourcing pipeline: given a single event map (which always has a `:type` key) and
the aggregate's current state, it returns the new state produced by applying that event.
It is called via `Enum.reduce(new_events, current_instance.state, &apply_event/2)`, so
the event is the first argument and the accumulated state is the second.

Provide one clause per event type:

- `:task_created` — the current state will be `nil`; build a fresh state map with the
  event's `title` and `priority`, `assignee` set to `nil`, and `status` set to `:created`.
- `:task_assigned` — set the state's `:assignee` to the event's `assignee`.
- `:task_started` — set the state's `:status` to `:in_progress`.
- `:task_completed` — set the state's `:status` to `:completed`.
- `:task_reopened` — reset the state's `:status` to `:created` and clear `:assignee` to `nil`.

Each clause takes the event as the first argument and the state as the second, and returns
the updated state map.

